rweightlifting 0.2.1
----------------
* Add additional days per week variable to programs
* Add new function adjust_schedule to place programmed workouts on specific days of the week; this function needs to be explicitly added to the dashboard, with some error checking (e.g., number of days selected should match days per week in program, or a warning message should appear)
* Drop Intensity tab from dashboard, since it's not ready for production yet
* Fix orientation bug in ggplot for rep PR view

rweightlifting 0.2.0
----------------
* Move data to inst/extdata per tidyverse package instructions
* Add @import directives to .R files to pass package checks
* Add .data$ references to tidyverse variables to pass package checks
* Remove intensity charts from dashboard, as the concept underlying the visualizations need refinement

rweightlifting 0.1.9
----------------
* Update readme file to github style
* Add novice linear progression and 4-day LP programs
* Change programming templates to define a deload schedule
  - User can select in dashboard number of cycles to go between deloads
  - Keeps dates in schedule on track
* Bug fixes

rweightlifting 0.1.8
----------------
* New programming template for 8-6-3 upper body with pyramid, 5-3-1 lower body with last set first, and a deload week

rweightlifting 0.1.7
----------------
* Added programming templates
* Wrote shiny dashboard tab for programming with templates
* roughed out shiny dashboard tab for custom programming with inputs

rweightlifting 0.1.6
----------------
* Vectorized one_rep_max and n_rep_max functions

rweightlifting 0.1.5
----------------
* Revised import function to import single files as well as directories
* Revised raw-data files to separate equipment and exercise variant (e.g., "bench,incline dumbbell" to "bench,dumbbell,incline"
* created programming functions that calculate all top sets (except reload weeks), a training max, and a one-rep max from a weightlifting log; uses rolling means, should provide for additional calculation options in the future
* created draft function for exercise descriptors, intended to be a library of all exercises so that exercise types can be matched to muscle groups or day groups (e.g., push/pull or upper/lower splits so that balance can be manipulated; incomplete


